parameters.description: Maximum phytoplankton growth rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum phytoplankton intrinsic growth rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); will be modulated by temperature via Q10

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake by phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation nutrient concentration for phytoplankton uptake (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Nutrient uptake efficiency (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton nutrient uptake efficiency (proportion 0-1)

parameters.description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate on phytoplankton at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); will be modulated by temperature via Q10

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for zooplankton grazing on phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation phytoplankton concentration for zooplankton grazing (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency of ingested phytoplankton (0-1)

parameters.description: Phytoplankton mortality rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton natural mortality rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); will be modulated by temperature via Q10

parameters.description: Zooplankton mortality rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton natural mortality rate at reference temperature T_ref (day^-1); will be modulated by temperature via Q10

parameters.description: Phytoplankton detritus recycling fraction (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fraction of dead phytoplankton biomass recycled to nutrients; remainder sinks out of mixed layer (0-1, typically 0.3-0.6)

parameters.description: Zooplankton waste recycling fraction (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fraction of dead zooplankton biomass recycled to nutrients; remainder sinks out of mixed layer (0-1, typically 0.5-0.8)

parameters.description: Surface light intensity (incident photosynthetically active radiation)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Surface irradiance available for photosynthesis; typical oceanic values range 50-400 W m^-2 depending on season and latitude; now estimable with realistic bounds

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for light-limited phytoplankton growth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Light intensity at which phytoplankton growth rate is half-maximal; typical values 20-50 W m^-2 for oceanic species

parameters.description: Background light attenuation coefficient (water and dissolved matter)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Light attenuation by pure seawater and dissolved materials; 0.02-0.04 m^-1 for clear oceanic waters, higher in coastal regions

parameters.description: Specific light attenuation coefficient for phytoplankton (self-shading)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Light attenuation per unit phytoplankton biomass; represents self-shading effect; typical values 0.01-0.05 m^2 (g C)^-1

parameters.description: Mixed layer depth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Depth of the surface mixed layer where plankton populations are well-mixed; varies seasonally from ~10-20 m (summer stratification) to 100-200 m (winter mixing)

parameters.description: Co-limitation exponent controlling interaction between nutrient and light limitation
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Co-limitation exponent: theta=1 gives Liebig's Law (minimum limitation), theta→∞ gives multiplicative co-limitation, theta=2-4 represents intermediate ecologically realistic co-limitation observed in phytoplankton cultures

parameters.description: Temperature coefficient for biological rates (Q10 formulation)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Q10 temperature coefficient: factor by which biological rates increase for a 10°C temperature increase; typical values for marine plankton are 1.5-3.0, with 2.0 being a common central estimate; currently uses T_ref as constant temperature until temperature data is provided

parameters.description: Reference temperature for biological rates
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Reference temperature at which the base biological rates (r_P, g_max, m_P, m_Z) are defined; typical oceanic mixed layer temperatures range 10-20°C in temperate regions; currently also used as constant temperature until temperature data is provided

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for nutrient observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of nutrient observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for phytoplankton observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of phytoplankton observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for zooplankton observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of zooplankton observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Time vector for observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observation time points in days

parameters.description: Observed nutrient concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed nutrient concentration in mixed layer (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Observed phytoplankton concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed phytoplankton biomass concentration (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Observed zooplankton concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed zooplankton biomass concentration (g C m^-3)
